<div class="content"><p>The RpcCloseEnum method closes the enumeration object
returned by <span><a href="f17f4b8d-8d52-4538-acf3-cdfbe581a99b" data-linktype="relative-path">RpcOpenEnum</a></span>. This
method MUST be called after RpcOpenEnum. No special permissions are required to
call this method.</p><dl>
<dd>
<div><pre> HRESULT RpcCloseEnum(
   [in, out] ENUM_HANDLE* phEnum
 );
</pre></div>
</dd></dl><p><b>phEnum: </b> The <span><a href="c41d3367-04c9-4c93-babf-9b5de834eb29#gt_5044babb-08e3-4bb9-bc12-fe8f542b05ee" data-linktype="relative-path">handle</a></span> to the
session enumeration object. This is of type <span><a href="15f02d59-200a-435d-a07b-055e1276d01c" data-linktype="relative-path">ENUM_HANDLE</a></span>.</p><p><b>Return Values: </b> The method MUST return S_OK
(0x00000000) on success; otherwise, it MUST return an implementation-specific
negative value.</p><dl>
<dd>
<table><thead>
  <tr>
   <th>
   <p>Return value/code</p>
   </th>
   <th>
   <p>Description</p>
   </th>
  </tr>
 </thead><tbody><tr>
  <td>
  <p>0x00000000</p>
  <p>S_OK</p>
  </td>
  <td>
  <p>Successful completion.</p>
  </td>
 </tr></tbody></table>
</dd></dl><p> </p></div>